        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="1052"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1052">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Potsdam/8–145</note>
                <head>No. 1052<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the British Delegation</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d1052fn1">This paper bears the following manuscript notation
                        by <persName corresp="#p_YCW1">Yost</persName>: “Br[itish] Proposal
                        presented to Conference Aug[ust] 1. <persName corresp="#p_SGIV1"
                            >Stalin</persName> asked for time to study”. See <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_570">pp. 570</ref>–<ref target="#pg_571"
                            >571</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-01">August 1,
                            1945</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Note</hi>
                </p>
                <p>It was agreed<note n="2" xml:id="d1052fn2">See <ref
                            target="frus1945Berlinv01#d433">vol. <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>,
                            document No. 433</ref>.</note> that the British and American Commanders
                    would provide 40,000 tons of food a month and 2,400 tons of coal a day for the
                    British and American Zones in Berlin for thirty days running from July 15th.
                    Pending the establishment of an agreement for the instalments of commodities to
                    be made available by the Soviet Government under paragraph 4 (<hi rend="italic"
                        >a</hi>) of the Reparations Agreement,<note n="3" xml:id="d1052fn3">See <ref
                            target="#d1383">document No. 1383, section <hi rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> the Control Council should be instructed to draw up
                    immediately a programme of the food, coal and fuel which will need to be
                    imported during the next six months into the Greater Berlin area to bring the
                    standard of the whole of the population of that area up to an agreed level.
                    These amounts will be furnished by the Soviet Government to the Greater Berlin
                    area as an advance delivery under paragraph 4 (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) of the
                    Reparations Agreement.</p>
            </div>
